{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PopulationGraph","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"PopulationGraph","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is the primary container for graph data in the Graphs library.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It manages a fixed set of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/Node","type":"reference"},{"text":" instances and multiple ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/EdgeSet","type":"reference"},{"text":" collections,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allowing quick switching between different connectivity patterns.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This design is optimized for use cases where you have a stable set of nodes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(such as populations, locations, or entities) but want to visualize different","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"relationships between them. Examples include:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Viewing different generations of an evolutionary algorithm"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Comparing networks at different statistical thresholds","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Switching between different types of relationships (genetic, geographic, etc.)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Basic Usage","anchor":"Basic-Usage","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Create nodes","var graph = PopulationGraph()","graph.addNode(Node(label: \"Pop A\", color: .blue))","graph.addNode(Node(label: \"Pop B\", color: .green))","graph.addNode(Node(label: \"Pop C\", color: .red))","","\/\/ Connect nodes by label","graph.connect(\"Pop A\", to: \"Pop B\", distance: 30)","graph.connect(\"Pop B\", to: \"Pop C\", distance: 25)","","\/\/ Use with simulation","let simulation = GraphSimulation()","simulation.load(graph)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Multiple Edge Sets","anchor":"Multiple-Edge-Sets","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Create multiple connectivity patterns","let generation1 = EdgeSet(name: \"Gen 1\", edges: [...])","let generation2 = EdgeSet(name: \"Gen 2\", edges: [...])","","graph.addEdgeSet(generation1)","graph.addEdgeSet(generation2)","","\/\/ Switch between them","graph.nextEdgeSet()     \/\/ Move to next","graph.setActiveEdgeSet(0)  \/\/ Jump to specific index","","\/\/ Update simulation with new edges","simulation.updateEdgeSet(graph.activeEdgeSet!)"],"syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/graphs\/populationgraph"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A data store for graph data with a fixed node set and multiple switchable edge sets."}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Creating-Graphs","title":"Creating Graphs","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/init(nodes:edgeSets:activeEdgeSetIndex:)","doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/init(nodes:edges:edgeSetName:)"]},{"anchor":"Graph-Properties","title":"Graph Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/nodes","doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/nodeCount","doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/edgeSets","doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/activeEdgeSetIndex","doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/PopulationGraph\/activeEdgeSet","doc:\/\/G